232.name: Chat with Xenthos: Girl Troubles
232.content:
[[Having some father-son bonding time up on Astral while Xenthos picks sparkleberry]]

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "O-K, O-K, what else, what else..."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "There was definitely a second thing that you brought up."

You have emoted: Gurashi continues to trail along, watching Xenthos work and seeming to take mental notes.

Faintly buzzing, you ask, "A second thing?"

Faintly buzzing, you ask Xenthos, "Eh? Do remember? what was it, did say?"

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "You did not."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "You said two things."

Looking very confused, you ask, "I did??"

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Ahhh uhhhhh the [[redacted]] thing was the most pressing."

Xenthos nods his head in agreement.

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Let's see... am going to try to temper responses to silly things, so they hopefully will happen... less..."

You have emoted: Gurashi suddenly looks up mid-counting on his fingers. "Oh." His mandibles click once. "So, uh."

Very stiff and awkward, you ask Xenthos, "Am having a .... girl trouble. Are any good with ... solving ...those?"

Xenthos purses his lips pensively, gazing off into the distance as he carefully gathers his thoughts.

You have emoted: Gurashi pretends to find something interesting in one of the many sparkleberry patches immediately after asking, scratching his chin.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "I don't now that I have ever helped much with a girl trouble, though I've had one or two of my own."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Ahhhhh, hah, am understanding."

You ponder the situation.

Carrying on awkwardly, still looking at the flowers, you say to Xenthos, "Well, uhm - she is not fate-touched.... or, from Glomdoring..."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist looks skeptical and says, "I see."

Waving his hand around, you say, "And don't see her so often anyway, so, am probably building up a lot in head, as tend to do."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "But, uhm."

Tapping together the fingertips of all four hands, you say to Xenthos, "She -kissed- me."

Xenthos tilts his head curiously at you.

Antennae twitching at the recollection, you say to Xenthos, "So anyway it was my first -ever- so, aheh, am still kind of wowee about it, which is probably not helping the head building, but, anyway."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Think the biggest problem is, after kissed, said had a.."

You stare ahead, looking utterly wounded.

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Ah, wife."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Ah."

(The Crux): Romaan (from the Prime Material Plane) says, "Timequake."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "I hate you timequake."
(The Shadow Kindred): Aurik says, "Pretty good, we have serious numbers."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Gurashi: *having heartfelt emotional talk*."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Lusternia: *timequake*."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "I hate you."

***TIMEQUAKE, THEN AFK FOR A FEW HOURS***

[[Returns to harvesting herbs with Xenthos, this time in Glom]]

You have emoted: Gurashi's mandibles click against his face as he plods along just a few steps behind Xenthos.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "...if am honest do not really remember what were talking about before timequake hit."

Faintly buzzing, you whisper, "Chervilll."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "It sounded as if we were talking about a woman who was greatly confused about the oaths she has taken."

You have emoted: Gurashi lets out the smallest of gasps. "Ah - no, do not think is anything malicious!" He defends quickly. "She is not ... she is a little..." He gestures with a hand, "....aloof...?"

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "I-I want to at least ask about it."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "It may not be malicious, but she does know what she has promised, one assumes?"

Faintly buzzing, you ask Xenthos, "Well yes but - do not know if her wife is still alive? Or if is a metaphorical wife?"

You have emoted: Gurashi waves his arms. "Are too many unknowns...!"

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Ah. So she is either breaking her promise, or she is stating untruths in an attempt to... what?"

Xenthos purses his lips pensively, gazing off into the distance as he carefully gathers his thoughts.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Is there an option that does not make her sound as if she is completely untrustworthy?"

You have emoted: Gurashi opens his mouth after each statement, but quickly shuts it to allow Xenthos to answer. Finally, he takes a step forward, nearly interrupting the faeling's harvesting. "I do not know if she knows everything that goes on in world."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Uhm, it is hard to explain."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Mm. So it seems."

You have emoted: Gurashi fidgets and fumbles, following along. "You are sounding dubious."

You chitter at Xenthos with energetic clicks of your mandibles.

You have emoted: Gurashi covers his face, heaving a great sigh.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "When you say you are unsure if she is aware of what is going on... you make it sound like she speaks just to speak. That she does not think about what she says. That she is unable to hold a thought, and from one moment to the next she might just vanish. Cannot be counted upon, cannot be trusted. If that is not what you mean, then yes, I fully agree that it is not easy to explain."

You blink.

You have emoted: Gurashi stares at Xenthos, at a loss for words.

You have emoted: Gurashi remains quiet for a long time, trailing many steps further back from Xenthos, head bowed in thought.

You think to yourself: ....is discouraging.

You think to yourself: ...does mean, only kind of persons who would like ...

The wind whistles eerily through the branches overhead.

You think to yourself: ...is persons not able to hold a thought?

You think to yourself: Persons that just speak to speak...?

You think to yourself: That kind of persons sounds like a fool... 

You think to yourself: ... ah ....

Finally breaking the excruciating silence, you say, "Are right."

You suddenly scoop up a glittering black rose.
A thorn upon a glittering black rose pricks your finger, and a drop of blood is absorbed into the stem.

You wince in pain.

You have emoted: Gurashi considers a glittering black rose thoughtfully.

You have emoted: Gurashi lowers his arm, still gripping the flower tight between his fingers. "Was really happy," He confesses quietly, slowing his steps.

You think to yourself: Am an idiot.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says to you, "I know that you and I have discussed Black Sorrow before. Perhaps this would be a good time to consider that aspect of Brother Crow's once more. Things do not always work out the way we want them to, or hope that they do."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says to you, "But they won't break you. You're stronger than that."

You have emoted: Gurashi's head bobs once as he nods, trailing miserably behind.

You think to yourself: Am such a fool.

(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Admin didn't start the event, so Gurashi has a heartbreak instead. :(."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Woe."
(The Shadow Kindred): Esei says, "Alas."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Look what they did."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Sobs."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Are you trying to make me cry."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Wait i started the conversation."

[[Lots of silent following]]

You have emoted: Gurashi bumps into Xenthos as they enter the next clearing, the clink of chitin on metal audible. "Oomph," He scrambles back. "M-many apologies."

Not having noticed the bump while he's concentrating on the herbs, Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Mm?"

You have emoted: Gurashi shakes his head.

Voice barely above a whisper, you ask, "Do think is still O-K to ask?"

Xenthos purses his lips pensively, gazing off into the distance as he carefully gathers his thoughts.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "If you need to for yourself, then aye. But it does not sound like the answer is going to change anything, does it? So keep that in mind when you do."

You have emoted: Gurashi sets his jaw tightly, exhaling.

Faintly buzzing, you whisper, "Do not like questions unanswered, even if do not like answers."

You twiddle your thumbs.

You think to yourself: Is how is.

You think to yourself: Is how is how is.

Xenthos nods his head at you.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "And that is fair."

You think to yourself: So is fine right.

You have emoted: Gurashi nods again, clenching his hands together tightly as he walks.

You think to yourself: So why do feel so sad.

You think to yourself: This is just a thing.

You pet Ilistala, an enormous leopard ingratiatingly.
A loud rumbling emanates from Ilistala as she rubs against you.

After another long while, still petting Ilistala, you say to Xenthos, "Uhm..."

You have emoted: Gurashi sniffs.

Ilistala, an enormous leopard inches bashfully over to you and nuzzles you tenderly.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says to you, "Aye?"

Quietly dazed, you say, "No, think was all had to say about it."

Nodding at Gurashi, Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "All right."

(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Woe."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Woe."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "You woe'd me."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "You reasoned me and now i'm woe."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Xenthos does reasons."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Ugh."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Me, a feelings kinda guy."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "If we were playing Lasers and Feelings."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "Xenthos would be 5 lasers and Gurashi would be 5 feelings."

Canting his head and sound almost annoyed, you ask Xenthos, "...guess one more question: when do I stop thinking about it?"

You carapace turns a bright shade of red as you blush.

Your eyes raise to the heavens as a look of hope flashes across your face.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Is the question 'when should I,' or 'when will I'?"

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Because they are two very different questions."

You twitch your mandibles as you voice a soft, curious chirr.

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Still have questions that want to ask."

Frazzled, you say, "So cannot stop thinking about."

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Oof, is -maddening-."

You twitch your mandibles as you voice a soft, curious chirr.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "It sounds like both are the same answer at least until you have had the questions answered."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Do you think that the questions ever will be answered?"

You nod your head at Xenthos.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "...yeah... somehow she keeps finding ways to find me. Or, people finding ways to... find us together."

You shuffle your feet uneasily.

Sheepishly, suddenly happy, you say to Xenthos, "Weee went ice skating... she is very good at skating...."

Ilistala, an enormous leopard ponders you thoughtfully, looking you up and down.

You think to yourself: Am not allowed.

You think to yourself: To feel this happy about it still.

You think to yourself: Because must let that go.

Ilistala, an enormous leopard stares at your feet.

Gently, you say to Ilistala, an enormous leopard, "Only fell down -once-, you would have been impressed."

Ilistala, an enormous leopard attempts to nudge you, but the distinct lack of ice does not yield the desired result.

Weakly staggering forward, you say to Ilistala, an enormous leopard, "Am sorry."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Ilistala, an enormous leopard, "Can only shuffle."

You tilt your head, gaze softening as you frown.

You have emoted: Gurashi offers Ilistala, an enormous leopard an apologetic pat on the head.

Ilistala, an enormous leopard inches bashfully over to you and nuzzles you tenderly.

Finally, after another terrible pause, you say to Xenthos, "So, yes, this has all been going on, in addition to things have already told about with Lord Silence and Lady of Roses's things..."

Xenthos nods his head at you.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Sounds... like many things to deal with at once."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "And, Lord of the Azure Flame is speaking to? And finding out that Lady Enchantress was at the party and took something - there have been many many worrisome things."

You have emoted: Gurashi nods quickly.

Chittering noisily, you say, "I have not yet resolved feelings towards Lord Silence. Am trying to be ... unafraid of, but, is so -cryptic-, and am not good at cryptic, and just want to make Him -happy-."

You shrug helplessly.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "All these Divines keep calling me 'interesting', it fills with waspssheeuuugh."

You have emoted: Gurashi chatters anxiously.

You think to yourself: I do not know what They all want from me.

You think to yourself: What any would...

[[Another long pause, lots of walkies]]

Quietly, you ask Xenthos, "Are quiet. Are... O-K?"

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Aye, just getting some colewort now."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "I think you said you needed some?"

You nod your head emphatically.

Faintly buzzing, you say, "...oh! Uh, yes."

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Have been using it in everything, heh."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "...my problems feel very... small in the grand scheme of things."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "And so is often hard to bring up - know have said before."
You flail about helplessly.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "But the problems that affect you always feel larger in your own head."

Fumbling, you say to Xenthos, "But hope know was not keeping anything from intentionally, just..."

You nod your head emphatically.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Yes - they feel very big and heavy."

Ilistala, an enormous leopard inches bashfully over to you and nuzzles you tenderly.

You have emoted: Gurashi frowns, wrapping his arms around Ilistala, an enormous leopard's neck and heaving a great sigh.

Still hugging Ilistala, you say to Xenthos, "You are a big, very important, very dedicated piece of Wyrden society and of Glomdoring, yes. But, you are also my dad, and so really, -really- promise will try to remember that, because cannot shake feeling that something terrible is coming, aha."

[[more walkies, started getting late irl so big sleepy all around]]

You think to yourself: Is so cold... ah, but the sky is so pretty....

You twitch your mandibles as you voice a soft, curious chirr.

You have emoted: Gurashi tightens his cloak around his shoulders, still damp from the earlier downpour.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Many thank yous for helping get coleworts."

You follow Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist southeast to sloping terrain.

Faintly buzzing, you ask Xenthos, "Can pay for?"

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "No."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Have... a cookie that is shaped like meee."

You have emoted: Gurashi holds the cookie up beside his face. "Observe."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Looks much alike."

You nod your head sagely.

You pet Ilistala, an enormous leopard ingratiatingly.
A loud rumbling emanates from Ilistala as she rubs against you.

You think to yourself: Am so tired...

You think to yourself: Insides are so tired.

You have emoted: Gurashi leans heavily against Ilistala, an enormous leopard as he follows behind, head tilted back thoughtfully.

[[Got a tell from someone asking why we were in Hifarae - plants!]]

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Ah - Miss Sadhe was asking me about why was here."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Ah."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "To steal all the colewort."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Or possibly to raid Lord Charune's realm."

Xenthos points accusingly at a twisting archway of vines.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "That's it right there."

You tilt your head curiously.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist smiles with a wink and says, "One step and off we go."

You follow Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist southeast to a valley edge.

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Oh."

Faintly buzzing, you ask, "But, we are not raiding His realm, correct?"

Faintly buzzing, you say, "Only want the coleworts...."

You twitch your mandibles as you voice a soft, curious chirr.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "That is correct."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "We just happened to be right at the entrance at the time."

You nod your head emphatically.

Faintly buzzing, you say, "We are not up to no good. Only merry plant picker peoples."

You have emoted: Gurashi gestures vaguely at the surrounding flora.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Yes. We are quite merry."

(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Merry."
(The Shadow Kindred): You say, "Gurashi: MEGA SKULK."
(The Shadow Kindred): Xenthos says, "We're gonna be merry OR ELSE."

You have emoted: Gurashi twiddles his thumbs, thoughtfully looking skywards before recognizing his surroundings.

Quietly, you say, "Oh. Hifarae." <-- I'm slow

Xenthos nods his head in agreement.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "More valleys here, and some hills too."

Quietly, you say, "Oh, am seeing."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "I think that's all I can do for the month."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "That is a lot of herbs."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Have some herbs."

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "That... WAS a lot of herbs."

Faintly buzzing, you ask Xenthos, "So many herbs - will you be set for a while, though...?"

Xenthos shakes his head.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Have much more to do."

Xenthos gives a group of 1000 colewort leaves to you.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Put that in your rift."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Don't lose it!"

You store 1000 colewort in the rift.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Oh... that is too much."

You boggle at Xenthos.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Was expecting maybe few hundred but..."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "That is a few hundred."

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Ten hundreds."

You follow Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist up to A peaceful glade.

You stare at Xenthos, eyes wide.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "A lot of hundreds... ah... a big kindness."

You let out a soft, buzzing sigh.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Many thank yous..."

Ilistala, an enormous leopard inches bashfully over to you and nuzzles you tenderly.

Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist says, "Be well, Gurashi."

You nod your head emphatically.

You reach out, wrapping all four arms around Ilistala, an enormous leopard as you pull her into a tight hug.
A loud rumbling emanates from Ilistala as she rubs against you.

Faintly buzzing, you say to Xenthos, "Goodnight Xenthos."

You cease to follow Spirit Warden Xenthos An'Ryshe, the Ebon Strategist.

Faintly buzzing, you ask, "If dream - hope they are good dreams?"

You nod your head emphatically.

You wave goodbye.

<-- leavey

# StackMob 5.0 Configuration file - by antiPerson and contributors.

# Most options can be customised for specific entity types, for details about this, see the end of this file.
# Asterisk meaning:
# (*) This option cannot be overridden in the 'custom' section at the end of this file.
# (**) The following option requires the use of Paper (https://papermc.io) because the API needed is not in Spigot.

stack:
  # The maximum size that a stack can have.
  max-size: 20
  # How often entities should be checked for stacking (in ticks. 20 ticks = 1 second) (*)
  interval: 100
  # The area around an entity for which applicable stacks should be found.
  # Format: [(x cord),(y cord),(z cord)]
  merge-range: [10,10,10]
  # Only begin to stack entities when this amount of entities are nearby.
  threshold:
    enabled: true
    amount: 10

# Names of worlds where there should be no stacking
worlds-blacklist: []
worlds-blacklist-invert: false
# Types of entity which should not stack
types-blacklist: []
types-blacklist-invert: false
# If the entity's spawns reason is listed below, do not stack.
reason-blacklist: []
reason-blacklist-invert: false

display-name:
  # The formatting of the name tag which is shown when the stack size is above the threshold.
  # Placeholders:
  # %type% - the entity's type
  # %size% - the size of the stack
  format: '&a%type% &d(%size%)'
  # Whether the display tag can only be seen when the player targets the entity.
  # Mode:
  # ALWAYS - The tag will always be visible as long as the entity is loaded.
  # HOVER - The tag will only be visible when the player hovers their crosshair on the entity.
  # NEARBY - The tag will only be visible when the player is in range of the entity. (more resource intensive)
  visibility: NEARBY
  # Options for when 'NEARBY' is used above. (*)
  nearby:
    # The range from which the tag should be visible.
    # Format: [(x cord),(y cord),(z cord)]
    range: [8,6,8]
    # How often (in ticks) the tag visibility status of an entity should be updated. (20 ticks = 1 second)
    interval: 20
  # Don't show the tag if the stack size of this entity if it is equal to or below the value specified.
  threshold: 1

# Whether entity specific traits (eg. profession, colour) should be segregated (*)
traits:
  sheep-color: true
  sheep-sheared: true
  slime-size: true
  horse-color: true

244.name: client
244.content:
-- VARIABLES
local host_id = os.computerID()
local serv_id
local id_found = false
local want_exit = false

-- FUNCTIONS

function find_id()
  rednet.broadcast("server_id", "server_id")
  serv_id = rednet.receive("server_id_response", 5)
  if serv_id ~= nil then
    id_found = true
  end
end

function join(server_id)
  rednet.send(server_id, "join", "join")
end

function leave(server_id)
  rednet.send(server_id, "leave", "leave")
  textutils.slowPrint("Closing client . . .")
  sleep(2)
  want_exit = true
end

function list(server_id)
  rednet.send(server_id, "list", "list")
  local id, list = rednet.receive("list_response", 5)
  print(list)
end

function message_send(server_id, message)
  rednet.send(server_id, message, "message")
end

function message_receive(message)
  print(message)
end

function input()
  write(">")
  local input = read()
  if string.sub(input, 0, 1) == "/" then
    if input == "/help" then
      print("/help for help")
      print("/exit for exit")
      print("/list for list")
    elseif input == "/exit" then
      leave(serv_id)
    elseif input == "/list" then
      list(serv_id)
    else
      print("Unknown command, type /help")
    end
  else
    message_send(serv_id, input)
  end
end
-- MAIN CODE
rednet.open("back")
while not id_found do
  textutils.slowPrint("Looking for a server . . .")
  find_id()
end
join(serv_id)
while true do
  event, param1, param2, param3 = os.pullEvent()
  if event == "rednet_message" then
    if param3 == "message" then
      message_receive(param2)
    end
  elseif event == "key" then
    input()
  end
  if want_exit then
    break
  end
end

249.name: server
249.content:
-- VARIABLES
local host_id = os.computerID()
local users = {}

-- FUNCTIONS
function user_joined(user_id)
  rednet.broadcast(user_id.." joined the server", "message")
  print(user_id.." joined the server")
  users[#users+1] = user_id
end

function user_left(user_id)
  local mess = user_id.." disconnected from the server"
  rednet.broadcast(mess, "message")
  print(user_id.." disconnected from the server")
  for i=1, #users do
    if users[i] == user_id then
      table.remove(users, i)
    end
  end
end

function id_request(user_id)
  rednet.send(user_id, host_id, "server_id_response")
  print(user_id.." requested server id")
end

function list_request(user_id)
  local mess = "Users on server: "
  for i=1, #users do
    mess = mess..users[i].." "
  end
  rednet.send(user_id, mess, "list_response")
  print(user_id.." requested user list")
end

function message_sent(user_id, message)
  rednet.broadcast(user_id.."- "..message, "message")
  print(user_id.."- "..message)
end
-- MAIN CODE
rednet.open("back")
rednet.broadcast("Server is online", "message")
print("Server is online")
while true do
  local event, param1, param2, param3 = os.pullEvent()
  if event == "rednet_message" then
    if param3 == "server_id" then
      id_request(param1)
    end
    if param3 == "join" then
      user_joined(param1)
    end
    if param3 == "leave" then
      user_left(param1)
    end
    if param3 == "list" then
      list_request(param1)
    end
    if param3 == "message" then
      message_sent(param1, param2)
    end
  end
  if event == "key" then
    write(">")
    local input = read()
    if input == "list" then
      if #users > 0 then
      local lista = "Users connected: "
      for i=1,#users do
        lista = lista..users[i].." "
      end
      print(lista)
      else
        print("There are no users")
      end
    elseif input == "exit" then
      rednet.broadcast("Server is offline", "message")
      textutils.slowPrint("Closing server . . .")
      break
    elseif input == "say" then
      write("Type your message: ")
      local messag = read()
      rednet.broadcast("server- "..messag, "message")
      print("server- "..messag)
    elseif input == "help" then
      print("list: shows user list")
      print("exit: closes server")
      print("say: allows you to say sth to chat")
    else
      print("Unknown command, type \"help\" for help")
    end
  end
end

251.content: After countless situations, arguments and disputes I have experienced many if not all situations possible. I have given my opinion to too many people to count and often resolved a situation from start to finish, I think my knowledge of the rules and community, long standing contribution to the server as a player and faction member to create role-play situations has given me the experience to "Officially" Help people and have the trust factor from players. Over the years I have been on and off the community but while on the community I have read through the rules multiple times, referenced them in situations and learnt them well as a general knowledge to myself. Yes I do have to check the rules on situations sometimes but doesn't everyone I often check the rule change log and will always resort to checking rules in situations necessary due to how often rules can fluctuate. I want to be that one that is available to help people and I will be motivated to do so, I don't have much to do when I'm not at work and I will find this something to keep me occupied while providing a service to the community I know and love. I might even go as far to say that I grown up on this community for the past 4 years, I have made countless friends here (Some I have actually met up with IRL) which just goes to show how much of an impact this server has had on my life and how much of my life I have spent getting to know it and experiencing different things.

Niniejszym raportem zwracam się z prośbą do Pana Komendanta oraz Pana Dowódcy o przeniesienie mnie do pełnienia dalszej służby w Jednostce SO.
 
[List Motywacyjny, Dlaczego chcesz dołączyć, Co wniesiesz ze sobą wraz z dołączeniem do jednostki]
Chce dolaczyc do Sheriff Office, przede wszystkim dlatego, by to cale hrabstwo bylo duzo bardziej bezpieczne.Na ulicach Los Santos przestepczosc dostala dosyc mocno zgnieciona pod butem naszego poteznego LSPD.
Jednak moim marzeniem jest, by nie tylko Los Santos bylo bezpieczne - marzy mi sie, by ludzie w calym hrabstwie czuli sie, i byli bezpieczni.Dlatego chce wstapic do SO,by pomagac ludziom nie tylko w Los Santos.
Jako osoba do jednostki wprowadza przede wszystkim siebie, i swoje umiejetnosci, ktore moze i nie sa wybitne, ale mysle, ze dorownuje wszystkim fuknkcjonariusza,a kilku z nich pewnie nawet przeganiam.
Staram sie zawsze lagodzic konflikty, i zawsze staram sie dazyc do porozumienia korzystnego dla obu stron, aczkolwiek robie tak, jezeli chodzi o konfflikty miedzy znajomymi z pracy.Jezeli negocjucje z 
gangsterem to zawsze staram sie, by negocjacje przebiegly na korzysc lspd i jestem stanowczy w tym, co robie.Moim zdaniem strzelam bardzo dobrze, gorzej z prowadzeniem ale tez daje rade.
Podsumowujac, uwazam, ze nadaje sie do SO i pelnilbym swoje stanowisko jako dobry szeryf.
 
 
 
 
Podpisano: Colin Dowell.

258.name: Untitled
258.content:
As mentioned above, "the end of genesis T.N.K.evolution In turbo type D" uses a modified form of the two-piece evaluation KP (King-Piece).  While KP looks at the relationship between either king and non-king pieces, HalfKP only looks at the relationship between one's own king and non-king pieces.
HalfKP is calculated with vectors from both one's own move and the opponent's move. In equation 17, v(p;active(p)) is the KP value with regard to one's own king on their move, while v(p;opponent(p)) is the KP value with regard to the opponent's king on their move. Therefore, though the term does not include information about the position of the enemy king, using HalfKP from both sides allows us to represent the pieces on the entire board. This reduces the calculation cost compared to using normal KP.

269.name: Untitled
269.content:
Esteemed Duke Eltan,

While I bear a vow of neutrality in the game of politics, that matter of neutrality does not prevent me from lending a hand to help alleviate diseases plaguing the good people of the realms. Pirates are one such disease, and it just so happens I might be well suited for help there.

You might remember me as then-proper Captain Dacino in absence of Captain Ostirel of the Whistling Wanderess during the Blight Wars, with my efforts contributing to war relief and the defeat of Lady Vernossa's fire ships meant to take down the Flame of Balduran. Now I have returned the mastery of the Whistling Wanderess to Captain Ostirel, but him being absent once more for duties untold, I have been assigned as her commander, and as her commander I volunteer her to serve the good people of Baldur's Gate against the plague that is opportunism at seas.

To achieve this, I would like to petition for a special letter of marquee.

It is special for I shall only hunt privateers hired against the local merchants, smugglers and illegitimate pirates. In other words, I will neither hunt recognised military or mercantile vessels of opposing nations, so as to preserve my political neutrality. Furthermore, the duration of this contract is to be until next year, or until the pirate threat abates - whichever comes first. Should the threat not abate next year, then I will seek renewal for another half-year.

The obligations I shall offer to observe:
Three days patrolling each quarter of a month, a total of twelve days active at sea minimum.
This means patrolling a radius around Baldur's Gate that encompasses five hundred nautical miles centred on Ulgoth's Beard.
Escorting vessels of millitary or mercantile nature from Candlekeep's latitude to Dragonspear's latitude.
Transporting goods and troops to the frontlines, as feasible for a vessel of the Whistling Wanderess's make and fit.
Turning in any and all non-elven pirates that surrendered or were otherwise captured in boarding combat to the Flaming Fist to judge with advice from the Temple of Tyr.
The Rights I wish to be observed:
Permission to use the drydocks and other services of port-side maintenance normally reserved for the Flaming Fist to repair damage suffered fighting pirates and a discount on such services of up to fifty thousand a month.
The right to take captured vessels as prize and turn them in for the Flaming Fist for a letter of guarantee.
The letter of guarantee will not be permitted to be turned in until the threat of devils abates. This is to reduce financial strain on Baldur's Gate from funding my activities. As an adventurer, I can pay for my crew and upkeep from my own private means. I also promise to observe Ilmatari care in turning in these letters of guarantee when the war passes, as to not strain the economy either when it needs a sigh of relief.
The right to plunder on any vessels captured marked as legitimate targets by the letter of marquee.
This includes removal of whatever equipment necessary at sea to repair damage required for a safe return to port, even if it leads to the need to scuttle the prize.
Any slaves rescued will be freed and allowed to go their own way once we return to Baldur's Gate.
Any equipment clearly marked as belonging to the Flaming Fist will be returned free of charge, except as discussed with the quartermaster receiving the shipment on a case-by-case basis to restore provisions or equipment lost in their liberation.
Any illegal goods will be returned to the Flaming Fist in exchange for a letter of guarantee, following rules established for taking prizes.
The right to refuse orders deemed illegal by the details of letter of marquee, the Whistling Wanderess's own code and the laws of Candlekeep and Doron Amar. These will be codified on the letter of marquee upon receiving it, but in essence are
No attacks against overwhelming odds without assistance (Wanderess code, preserving life of sailors)
All elven pirates are to be judged by the clergy of the Seldarine, failing that, the councillors of Doron Amar.
No knowing destruction of knowledge. Any lore captured must be returned to Candlekeep.
No participation in wars between Baldur's Gate and a legitimate nation. Privateers hired by a legitimate nation are an exception.
The right to attend to matters of defending Doron Amar and En Dharasha Everae and Candlekeep, even if it leads to less days patrolling within the given time frame. Provided the opportunity to rectify this, it will be done perhaps as six days of patrol in a given quarter over three.

I thank you for the consideration,
Acting-Captain Lafali'Atria-Hoihe Dacino of the Whistling Wanderess.

ELIKSIR NA CZYRAKI

Składniki: 6 kłów węża, 4 rogate ślimaki, 2 kolce jeżozwierza

Część 1
1. Dodać 6 kłów węża do naczynia.
2. Rozgnieść na drobny proszek za pomocą tłuczka.
3. Dodać 4 szczypty proszku do kociołka.
4. Ogrzewać przez 10 sekund w temperaturze 250 °C.
5. Pomachać różdżką.
6. Zostawić na 5-10 minut.
 
Część 2
7. Dodać 4 rogate ślimaki do kociołka.
8. Zdjąć kociołek z ognia przed dodaniem następnych składników.
9. Dodać 2 kolce jeżozwierza do kociołka.
10. Wymieszać 5 razy w prawo.
11. Pomachać różdżką zgodnie z ruchem wskazówek zegara.

306.name: Untitled
306.content:
Hey folks!

**Who we are..**
We are Aspire! A community that has been around since the early days of WoW.
We originate from the server Bloodfeather, back in 2005. And since then we've killed just about everything across most expansions (and have even dipped into other MMOs).
Ofcourse the core raid team have been switched around several times during the years, the leadship is stil core members from original Vanilla.

**Progression!**
I guess it goes without saying we have 11/11 bosses on farm.
Our best timed Molten Core run clocked in at 54 minutes with a standard comp of mixed Melee and Casters.
We do split 20/20 Onyxia runs aswell.

**What we are looking for.**
At the tail end of the tier 1 content a few players have dropped of and we're looking to fill the ranks with some new members.
We are mainly looking for dedicated players, with good raiding experiance and good insight and knowlage of the game. Gear is a plus but not a major factor. Gear is easy to get!

At the moment we're in demand of:
Holy Priests
Fury Warriors (can never have too many, ey?)
Rogue

However, we're always keen to listen to any players story, regardless of class if they think we're a good fit!

**When do we raid?**
Currently in the Tier 1 content with alternate the Molten Core runs between Sunday and Wednesday so people have 1,5 week of PVPing and Farming. And ofcourse we slay Onyxia whenever she lets us.
Once BWL drops we will pick up the scedual again and raid the folloing days.

Wednesday - 19:00 - 23:00
Sunday -   19:00 - 23:00

Sunday will likely be the progression raid and Wednesday we do MC, Onyxia and start picking of bosses in BWL.

**How is loot distrubuted?**
We are using Loot Council, and have done for several years.
When an item drop, the players link the item they wish to replace and officers then discuss where the item ends up.
Multiple factors decide who gets the item, such as useage of consumables, attendance, using the correct spec, enchants, performance. etc.

In the end we're looking to gear the guild as a whole.

**What we wish to see from our players!**
Well, the Loot Council part covered most of it I guess it bears repeating.
We wish to see players have a good understanding of thier class, and trying to continue discuss and learn the depths of thier class. Meaning players show up in an appropriate spec.
Getting the best gear possible outside of raids.
Using a reansonable ammount of consumables.
Enchanting the currently used gear, and doing the same when receiving new items.

**A few words about us..**
We have a very experianced officer team that have seen all sides of WoW and can with confidence say we will lead the guild trough all raiding content in WoW Classic.
While we try to keep raiding on a more serious note, we're still enjoying ourselfs during raids. We have no rules as to who can and cannot talk, tough ofcourse the officers do most of the chatter during boss encounters.
Outside of raids most people are quite talkative in both Guild chat and on Discord. There's usually a dungeon run or two every night that people can tag along in. We have quite a few altaholics in the guild.

**Still not convinced?**
Here have some videos from our misadventures! Our in-house video creator have been seen on r/wowclassic multiple times so some you might have seen before.

[WoW Classic Shenanigans](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=smfA_INpX88)
[Molten Core Adventures](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G39Nr958mNA)
[Dungeons with DataDood](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mLJOf97as_A)
[Our first Rag kill in Classic](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wojlQePgBqI&t=)
[Kael'thas Sunstrider from original TBC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ubf-JVQxoKY&list=PL1BFFE06FAB0964E1&index=16) 
[Playlist](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL1BFFE06FAB0964E1)

**Wanna join?**

Feel free to speak to an offcer at Discord or send us a whisper ingame and we'll have a chat!

*Ingame namn - Discord tag*
Datadood  - DataDood#5267
Agireda - Cerale#0038
Elakaspenen - Mal#3855
Shaka - Shaka#6521
Sická - Sicka#9245

Or just pop your head into our Discord server and say hi!
Thanks for taking your time reading this and we hope to hear from future members soon!
https://discord.gg/nh5u7TZ

```{r}
library("readxl")
library(glmnet)
data <- read_excel("spambase.xlsx")
#set.seed(12345)
#id <- sample(1:n, floor(n*0.5))
#train <- data[id,]
#test <- data[-id,]

B <- 100
n <- nrow(data)
#b1 <- list()
#b2 <- list()

#for (i in 1:B)
#{
#  b1[[i]] <- train[sample(1:nrow(train), n, replace = TRUE),]
#  b2[[i]] <- train[sample(1:nrow(train), n, replace = TRUE),]
#}

p <- ncol(data[,!names(data) %in% c("Spam")])
q1 <- round(p/2)
q2 <- round(p/2)
nfolds <- 4

#lambda=seq(0,10,length.out=1000)

beta_hat <- rep(0, p)
names(beta_hat) <- colnames(data[,!names(data) %in% c("Spam")])

counts <- rep(0, p) # NEW LINE
names(counts) <- colnames(data[,!names(data) %in% c("Spam")]) # NEW LINE
set.seed(12345) # NEW LINE

for (i in 1:B)
{
  #b <- b1[[i]]
  b <- data[sample(n, n, replace = TRUE),] # NEW LINE
  
  x <- as.matrix(b[,!names(b) %in% c("Spam")])
  #set.seed(12345)
  x <- x[,sample(1:ncol(x), q1)]
  y <- as.matrix(b[,"Spam"])
  lasso_cv <- cv.glmnet(x=x,y=y, alpha=1, nfolds=nfolds, family = "binomial")
  #lambda_min <- lasso_cv$lambda.min
  #lasso <- glmnet(x=x, y=y, alpha = 1, lambda = lambda_min)
  #coef <- coef(lasso)
  coef <- coef(lasso_cv, s = "lambda.min") # NEW LINE

  dimnames <- coef@Dimnames[1][[1]]
  for (j in 2:length(coef))
    {
    beta_hat[dimnames[j]] <- beta_hat[dimnames[j]]+coef[j]
    counts[dimnames[j]] <- counts[dimnames[j]]+1 # NEW LINE
  }
}
# for ( i in 1:length(counts)){
#   counts[i] <- ifelse(counts[i] == 0, 1, counts[i]) # NEW LINE
# }


importance <- abs(beta_hat/counts)
beta_hat <- rep(0, p)
names(beta_hat) <- colnames(data[,!names(data) %in% c("Spam")])
intercept <- 0
counts <- rep(0, p) # NEW LINE
names(counts) <- colnames(data[,!names(data) %in% c("Spam")]) # NEW LINE
set.seed(12345) # NEW LINE


for (i in 1:B)
{
  #b <- b2[[i]]
  
  b <- data[sample(n, n, replace = TRUE),] # NEW LINE

  x <- as.matrix(b[,!names(b) %in% c("Spam")])
  #set.seed(12345)
  x <- x[,sample(1:ncol(x), q2, prob = importance)]
  y <- as.matrix(b[,"Spam"])
  lasso_cv <- cv.glmnet(x=x,y=y, alpha=1, nfolds=nfolds, family = "binomial")
  #lambda_min <- lasso_cv$lambda.min
  #lasso <- glmnet(x=x, y=y, alpha = 1, lambda = lambda_min)
  #coef <- coef(lasso)
  coef <- coef(lasso_cv, s = "lambda.min") # NEW LINE

  dimnames <- coef@Dimnames[1][[1]]
  for (j in 2:length(coef))
    {
    beta_hat[dimnames[j]] <- beta_hat[dimnames[j]]+coef[j]
    counts[dimnames[j]] <- counts[dimnames[j]]+1 # NEW LINE
  }
  intercept <- intercept + coef[1]
}

for ( i in 1:length(counts)){
  counts[i] <- ifelse(counts[i] == 0, 1, counts[i]) # NEW LINE
}

beta_hat <- beta_hat/counts
intercept <- intercept/B
```

```{r}
predict_own <- function(x, weights, intercept)
{
  predictions <- vector(length = nrow(x))
  for (i in 1:nrow(x))
  {
   #predictions[i] <- ifelse(sum(x[i,]*weights)+intercept < 0.5, 0, 1)
    odds <- sum(x[i,]*weights)+intercept # NEW LINE
    prob <- 1/(1+exp(-odds)) # NEW LINE
    predictions[i] <- ifelse(prob > 0.5, 0, 1) # NEW LINE

  }
  return(predictions)
}

x <- data[,!names(data) %in% c("Spam")]
y <- t(data[,"Spam"])
predictions <- predict_own(x, beta_hat, intercept)

importance <- sort(importance, decreasing = TRUE)
barplot(importance[1:10], ylab = "Importance", xlab = "Feature")
confusion_matrix <- table(y, predictions)
confusion_matrix
cat("Accuracy: ", sum(diag(confusion_matrix))/sum(confusion_matrix))
```

import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions.udf
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import spark.implicits._
import java.time.LocalDate
import java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter
import java.sql.Timestamp

 
 
 




// DYSTANS
val mainDataCentral_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataCentral.csv").
 cache();
val mainDataEastern_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataEastern.csv").
 cache();
val mainDataMountain_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataMountain.csv").
 cache();
val mainDataPacific_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataPacific.csv").
 cache();
val allMainData_DS = mainDataCentral_DS.
 union(mainDataEastern_DS).
 union(mainDataMountain_DS).
 union(mainDataPacific_DS).
 dropDuplicates(Array("ID"));

 val uniqeDistances = allMainData_DS.dropDuplicates(Array("Distance(mi)")).select("Distance(mi)");

 def getId = (dystans: Float) => {
    if (dystans == 0) 0
    else if (dystans < 1) 1
    else if (dystans < 10) 2
    else 3
}

val getIdUDF = udf(getId)

val kategorie_DS = Seq((0, "0"), (1, "Ponizej 1 mili"), (2, "Ponizej 10 mil"), (3, "Powyzej 10 mil")).toDF("id_k", "kategoria")

val distances_DS_temp = uniqeDistances.
 withColumnRenamed("Distance(mi)", "dystans").
 withColumn("id", getIdUDF($"dystans")).
 select("id","dystans")
 
val distances_DS = distances_DS_temp.
 join(kategorie_DS, distances_DS_temp("id").equalTo(kategorie_DS("id_k")), "leftouter").
 select("id","dystans", "kategoria")
 
 
 ////////////////////////////POGODA///////////////////////////
val weather_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", false).option("inferSchema", true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/weather.txt").cache();
 
val regexWeather = """(?<=Weather Condition: ).+""".r
val regexTimestamp="""[0-9]{4}-(0[1-9]|1[0-2])-(0[1-9]|[1-2][0-9]|3[0-1]) (2[0-3]|[01][0-9]):[0-5][0-9]:[0-5][0-9]""".r
val regexCode = """(?<=airport )[A-Z0-9]{4}""".r
 
val GetWeather: String => String = regexWeather.findFirstIn(_).get
val GetDate: String => String = regexTimestamp.findFirstIn(_).get
val GetCode: String => String = regexCode.findFirstIn(_).get
 
val getWeatherUDF = udf(GetWeather)
val getDateUDF = udf(GetDate)
val getCodeUDF = udf(GetCode)
 
 
val weather_data = weather_DS.withColumnRenamed("_c8", "weather").
withColumnRenamed("_c0", "dateCol").
withColumn("date", getDateUDF($"dateCol").cast("timestamp")).
withColumn("Code", getCodeUDF($"dateCol")).
withColumn("weather", getWeatherUDF($"weather")).
select("weather", "date", "Code")

val weatherTab_DS = weather_DS.withColumnRenamed("_c8", "weather").
withColumn("weather", getWeatherUDF($"weather")).
select("weather").dropDuplicates("weather")

val w = Window.orderBy("weather")
val weather_with_id = weatherTab_DS.withColumn("id", row_number().over(w))
val weather_wymiar = weather_with_id.withColumnRenamed("weather", "nazwa").select("nazwa", "id")

//////////////////////////GEO/////////////////////////////

val geoDataCentral_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/geoDataCentral.csv").cache
    val geoDataEastern_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/geoDataEastern.csv").cache
    val geoDataMountain_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/geoDataMountain.csv").cache
    val geoDataPacific_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/geoDataPacific.csv").cache
    val allGeoData_DS = geoDataCentral_DS
    // .union(geoDataEastern_DS).union(geoDataMountain_DS).union(geoDataPacific_DS)

 ////////////////////////FACTS DATA//////////////////////////


 val main_Central_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).
 option("inferSchema", true).
 option("multiline", value= true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataCentral.csv").cache().select(
 substring($"Start_Time", 0, 10).as("Start_Date"),
 $"Start_Time",
 $"End_Time",
 $"Severity",
 $"Distance(mi)",
 $"Zipcode",
 $"Airport_Code"
 )
 
 main_Central_DS.show()
 
val main_Eastern_DS =  spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).
 option("inferSchema", true).
 option("multiline", value= true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataEastern.csv").cache().select(
 substring($"Start_Time", 0, 10).as("Start_Date"),
 $"Start_Time",
 $"End_Time",
 $"Severity",
 $"Distance(mi)",
 $"Zipcode",
 $"Airport_Code"
 )
 
val main_Mountain_DS =  spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).
 option("inferSchema", true).
 option("multiline", value= true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataMountain.csv").cache().select(
 substring($"Start_Time", 0, 10).as("Start_Date"),
 $"Start_Time",
 $"End_Time",
 $"Severity",
 $"Distance(mi)",
 $"Zipcode",
 $"Airport_Code"
 )
 
val main_Pacific_DS = spark.read.format("org.apache.spark.csv").
 option("header", true).
 option("inferSchema", true).
 option("multiline", value= true).
 csv("/user/gedin8/labs/spark/mainDataPacific.csv").cache().select(
 substring($"Start_Time", 0, 10).as("Start_Date"),
 $"Start_Time",
 $"End_Time",
 $"Severity",
 $"Distance(mi)",
 $"Zipcode",
 $"Airport_Code"
 )
 
val main_All_DS=main_Central_DS
// .union(main_Eastern_DS).union(main_Mountain_DS).union(main_Pacific_DS)


////////////////////////////////TEMPORARY_TABLES/////////////////////////

val pom_dist_DS = distances_DS.withColumnRenamed("id", "id_dist").select("id_dist", "dystans", "kategoria");

val pom_geo_DS = allGeoData_DS.withColumnRenamed("Zipcode", "geoZipcode").select("geoZipcode", "State")

val pom_weather_wymiar = weather_wymiar.withColumnRenamed("id", "id_weather").withColumnRenamed("nazwa", "nazwa_pogody").select("id_weather", "nazwa_pogody")

val pom_weather_DS = weather_data.
withColumnRenamed("Code", "w_code").
withColumnRenamed("date", "w_date").
join(pom_weather_wymiar, $"weather" === $"nazwa_pogody").
select("w_code", "w_date", "weather", "id_weather");

/////////////////////////CREATE FACTS//////////////////////
 
val all_Facts = main_All_DS.
join(pom_dist_DS, $"Distance(mi)" === $"dystans").
join(pom_geo_DS, $"Zipcode" === $"geoZipcode").
join(pom_weather_DS, unix_timestamp($"w_date")>=unix_timestamp($"Start_Time") && unix_timestamp($"w_date")<=unix_timestamp($"End_Time") && $"w_code" === $"Airport_Code", "LeftOuter").
dropDuplicates("Start_Time").
select(
    $"Start_Date".as("Date"),
    $"Start_Time",
    $"End_Time",
    $"Severity",
    $"Distance(mi)".as("Distance"),
    $"id_dist".as("Distance_Category"),
    $"id_weather",
    $"State").
    withColumn("Length_in_sec", (unix_timestamp($"End_Time") - unix_timestamp($"Start_Time"))).
    groupBy($"Date",
    $"State",
    $"Severity",
    $"Distance_Category"
    ,$"id_weather"
    ).
    agg(count($"Severity").as("Accidents_Count"),
    sum("Distance").as("sum_Distance"),
    sum("Length_in_sec").as("sum_Duration_Time")
    ).drop("Start_Time",
    "geoZipcode",
    "Zipcode",
    "End_Time",
    "Distance",
    "Length_in_sec",
    "Airport_Code"
    )
   
all_Facts.show()
//all_Facts.write.insertInto("etl_hd.fact")

-- This script has been converted to FE by KeyUsbr
 
 
if game:GetService("RunService"):IsClient() then error("Script must be server-side in order to work; use h/ and not hl/") end
local Player,Mouse,mouse,UserInputService,ContextActionService = owner
do
    print(" Translated to FE by astijus206")
    script.Parent = Player.Character
 
    --RemoteEvent for communicating
    local Event = Instance.new("RemoteEvent")
    Event.Name = "UserInput_Event"
 
    --Fake event to make stuff like Mouse.KeyDown work
    local function fakeEvent()
        local t = {_fakeEvent=true,Connect=function(self,f)self.Function=f end}
        t.connect = t.Connect
        return t
    end
 
    --Creating fake input objects with fake variables
    local m = {Target=nil,Hit=CFrame.new(),KeyUp=fakeEvent(),KeyDown=fakeEvent(),Button1Up=fakeEvent(),Button1Down=fakeEvent()}
    local UIS = {InputBegan=fakeEvent(),InputEnded=fakeEvent()}
    local CAS = {Actions={},BindAction=function(self,name,fun,touch,...)
        CAS.Actions[name] = fun and {Name=name,Function=fun,Keys={...}} or nil
    end}
    --Merged 2 functions into one by checking amount of arguments
    CAS.UnbindAction = CAS.BindAction
 
    --This function will trigger the events that have been :Connect()'ed
    local function te(self,ev,...)
        local t = m[ev]
        if t and t._fakeEvent and t.Function then
            t.Function(...)
        end
    end
    m.TrigEvent = te
    UIS.TrigEvent = te
 
    Event.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(plr,io)
        if plr~=Player then return end
        if io.isMouse then
            m.Target = io.Target
            m.Hit = io.Hit
        else
            local b = io.UserInputState == Enum.UserInputState.Begin
            if io.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton1 then
                return m:TrigEvent(b and "Button1Down" or "Button1Up")
            end
            for _,t in pairs(CAS.Actions) do
                for _,k in pairs(t.Keys) do
                    if k==io.KeyCode then
                        t.Function(t.Name,io.UserInputState,io)
                    end
                end
            end
            m:TrigEvent(b and "KeyDown" or "KeyUp",io.KeyCode.Name:lower())
            UIS:TrigEvent(b and "InputBegan" or "InputEnded",io,false)
        end
    end)
    Event.Parent = NLS([==[
    local Player = game:GetService("Players").LocalPlayer
    local Event = script:WaitForChild("UserInput_Event")
 
    local UIS = game:GetService("UserInputService")
    local input = function(io,a)
        if a then return end
        --Since InputObject is a client-side instance, we create and pass table instead
        Event:FireServer({KeyCode=io.KeyCode,UserInputType=io.UserInputType,UserInputState=io.UserInputState})
    end
    UIS.InputBegan:Connect(input)
    UIS.InputEnded:Connect(input)
 
    local Mouse = Player:GetMouse()
    local h,t
    --Give the server mouse data 30 times every second, but only if the values changed
    --If player is not moving their mouse, client won't fire events
    while wait(1/30) do
        if h~=Mouse.Hit or t~=Mouse.Target then
            h,t=Mouse.Hit,Mouse.Target
            Event:FireServer({isMouse=true,Target=t,Hit=h})
        end
    end]==],Player.Character)
    Mouse,mouse,UserInputService,ContextActionService = m,m,UIS,CAS
end

local plr = owner
function exe(cmd)
game:GetService'Players'.LocalPlayer.PlayerGui.SB_DataTransfer.SB_CommandRemote.Value = cmd
end
local adornees
local destroyit = false
local lasttarget 
local currenttarget

mouse.Button1Down:connect(function()
	if mouse.Target then
	if mouse.Target.Parent.ClassName == "Model" then
	currenttarget = mouse.Target.Parent
	lasttarget = mouse.Target.Parent
	adornees = Instance.new("Model",plr.Character)
	for i,v in pairs(mouse.Target.Parent:GetChildren()) do
		local s = Instance.new("SelectionBox",adornees)
		if v:IsA("Part") then
			if v.Name == "Torso" then

	end

	end

end)
game:GetService('UserInputService').InputBegan:connect(function(input,processed)
	if mouse.Target and destroyit == true then
	if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.C then
		--currenttarget:Destroy()
		for i,v in pairs(currenttarget:GetChildren()) do
			if v:IsA("LocalScript") then
				local c = v

				c.Name = "Stolen"
				exe('local a = '..v:GetFullName()..':Clone() a.Parent = getfenv().owner.Character print(a.Parent)')
				print(c.Parent)

end)
mouse.Button1Up:connect(function()

end)

      for i = 1, math.floor(tf / frame) do
        Heartbeat:Fire()
      end
      tf = tf - frame * math.floor(tf / frame)
    end
  end)
  function swait(num)

      end

  end

    p.TopSurface, p.BottomSurface, p.LeftSurface, p.RightSurface, p.FrontSurface, p.BottomSurface = 10, 10, 10, 10, 10, 10
  end
  function makepart(color, name, reflec, mater, parnt, cfram)
    local port = Instance.new("Part")
    port.BrickColor = BrickColor.new(color)
    port.Name = name
    nooutline(port)
    port.Reflectance = reflec
    port.Material = mater
    port.Anchored = false
    port.CanCollide = false
    port.Locked = true
    port.Size = Vector3.new(0.2, 0.2, 0.2)
    port.Parent = parnt
    return port
  end
  function makemesh(meshtype, scale, meshid, parent)
    local mes = Instance.new("SpecialMesh")
    mes.MeshType = meshtype
    mes.Scale = scale
    if meshtype == "FileMesh" then
      mes.MeshId = meshid
    end
    mes.Parent = parent
    return mes
  end
  function makeweld(parent, p0, p1, c0, c1)
    local wel = Instance.new("Weld")
    wel.Part0 = p0
    wel.Part1 = p1
    wel.C0 = c0
    if c1 ~= nil then
      wel.C1 = c1
    end
    wel.Parent = parent
    return wel
  end
  function smokz(prnt)
    s = Instance.new("Smoke")
    s.Color = Color3.new(1, 1, 1)
    s.Enabled = false
    s.Name = "smok"
    s.Opacity = 0.5
    s.RiseVelocity = 0.2
    s.Size = 0.1
    s.Parent = prnt
  end
  function glow(tz, paz, smokinz, length)
    if tz.Parent:FindFirstChildOfClass("Humanoid") and paz.Transparency == 1 then
      do
        local s = Instance.new("Sound")
        s.SoundId = "rbxassetid://298181829"
        s.Volume = 0.25
        s.Pitch = math.random(9, 11) / 10
        s.Parent = paz
        s:Play()
        paz.Transparency = 0.7
        if smokinz == true then
          paz.smok.Enabled = true
        end
        delay(length, function()
          paz.Transparency = 1

  function makeglow()
    for _, p in pairs(chr:GetChildren()) do
      if p.ClassName == "Accessory" then
        do
          local h = p:FindFirstChildOfClass("Part")
          local nh = h:Clone()
          nh.Parent = nil
          nh.CFrame = h.CFrame
          nh.Transparency = 1
          nh.Name = "Glow"
          nh.Material = "Neon"
          nh.BrickColor = BrickColor.new("New Yeller")
          nh.CustomPhysicalProperties = PhysicalProperties.new(0.2, 0.3, 0.5)
          nh.Parent = h
          makeweld(nh, nh, h, cf(0, 0, 0))
          local m = nh:FindFirstChildOfClass("SpecialMesh")
          m.Scale = m.Scale + Vector3.new(0.06, 0.06, 0.06)
          m.TextureId = ""
          smokz(nh)
          nh.Touched:connect(function(po)
            glow(po, nh, true, 0.8)
          end)
        end
      elseif p.ClassName == "Part" and p ~= hrp then
        do
          local n = p:Clone()
          n.Parent = nil
          n.Transparency = 1
          n.Material = "Neon"
          n.Name = "Glow"
          n.BrickColor = BrickColor.new("New Yeller")
          n.CFrame = p.CFrame
          n.CustomPhysicalProperties = PhysicalProperties.new(0.2, 0.3, 0.5)
          n.Parent = p
          makeweld(n, n, p, cf(0, 0, 0))
          smokz(n)
          n.Touched:connect(function(po)
            glow(po, n, true, 0.8)
          end)
          if n:FindFirstChildOfClass("Decal") then
            n:FindFirstChildOfClass("Decal"):Destroy()
          end
          if p:FindFirstChildOfClass("SpecialMesh") then
            local c = p:FindFirstChildOfClass("SpecialMesh"):Clone()
            c.Parent = nil
            c.Scale = c.Scale + Vector3.new(0.05, 0.05, 0.05)
            c.Parent = n
          else
            local m = Instance.new("BlockMesh")
            m.Scale = Vector3.new(1.05, 1.025, 1.05)
            if p == tors then
              m.Scale = Vector3.new(1.05, 1.05, 1.05)
            end
            m.Parent = n
          end
        end
      end
    end
  end
  makeglow()
  function fglow(glopart, duration)
    for _ = 1, 4 do
      swait()
      glopart.Transparency = glopart.Transparency - 0.075
    end
    delay(duration, function()
      for _ = 1, 4 do
        swait()
        glopart.Transparency = glopart.Transparency + 0.075
      end
    end)
  end
  function lerpz(joint, prop, cfrmz, alp)
    joint[prop] = joint[prop]:lerp(cfrmz, alp)
  end

  end

local acos = math.acos
local sqrt = math.sqrt
local Vec3 = Vector3.new
local fromAxisAngle = CFrame.fromAxisAngle

local function toAxisAngle(CFr)
        local X,Y,Z,R00,R01,R02,R10,R11,R12,R20,R21,R22 = CFr:components()
        local Angle = math.acos((R00+R11+R22-1)/2)
        local A = (R21-R12)^2+(R02-R20)^2+(R10-R01)^2
        A = A == 0 and 0.00001 or A
        local B = (R21-R12)^2+(R02-R20)^2+(R10-R01)^2
        B = B == 0 and 0.00001 or B
        local C = (R21-R12)^2+(R02-R20)^2+(R10-R01)^2
        C = C == 0 and 0.00001 or C
        local x = (R21-R12)/sqrt(A)
        local y = (R02-R20)/sqrt(B)
        local z = (R10-R01)/sqrt(C)
        return Vec3(x,y,z),Angle
end

function ApplyTrig(Num,Func)
        local Min,Max = Func(0),Func(1)
        local i = Func(Num)
        return (i-Min)/(Max-Min)
        --[[if Func == "sin" then
                return (math.sin((1-Num)*math.pi)+1)/2
        elseif Func == "cos" then
                return (math.cos((1-Num)*math.pi)+1)/2
        end]]
end

function LerpCFrame(CFrame1,CFrame2,Num)
        local Vec,Ang = toAxisAngle(CFrame1:inverse()*CFrame2)
        return CFrame1*fromAxisAngle(Vec,Ang*Num) + (CFrame2.p-CFrame1.p)*Num
end

function Crater(Torso,Radius)
        spawn(function()
        local Ray = Ray.new(Torso.Position,Vector3.new(0,-1,0)*10)
        local Ignore = {}
        for i,v in pairs(game:GetService("Players"):GetPlayers()) do
                if v.Character ~= nil then
                        Ignore[#Ignore+1] = v.Character
                end
        end
        local Hit,Pos,SurfaceNorm = workspace:FindPartOnRayWithIgnoreList(Ray,Ignore)
        if Hit == nil then return end
        local Parts = {}
        for i = 1,360,10 do
                local P = Instance.new("Part",Torso.Parent)
                P.Anchored = true
                P.FormFactor = "Custom"
                P.BrickColor = Hit.BrickColor
                P.Material = Hit.Material
                P.TopSurface = "Smooth"
                P.BottomSurface = "Smooth"
                P.Size = Vector3.new(5,10,10)*(math.random(80,100)/100)
                P.CFrame = ((CFrame.new(Pos,Pos+SurfaceNorm)*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(90),0,0))-Vector3.new(0,7,0))*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(math.random(-50,50)),math.rad(math.random(-50,50)),math.rad(math.random(-50,50)))
                Parts[#Parts+1] = {P,P.CFrame,((CFrame.new(Pos,Pos+SurfaceNorm)*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(90),0,0))-Vector3.new(0,1,0))*CFrame.Angles(0,math.rad(i),0)*CFrame.new(0,0,-Radius)*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(math.random(-50,-20)),math.rad(math.random(-15,15)),math.rad(math.random(-15,15))),P.Size}
                if math.random(0,5) == 0 then -- rubble
                        local P = Instance.new("Part",Torso.Parent)
                        P.Anchored = true
                        P.FormFactor = "Custom"
                        P.BrickColor = Hit.BrickColor
                        P.Material = Hit.Material
                        P.TopSurface = "Smooth"
                        P.BottomSurface = "Smooth"
                        P.Size = Vector3.new(2,2,2)*(math.random(80,100)/100)
                        P.CFrame = ((CFrame.new(Pos,Pos+SurfaceNorm)*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(90),0,0))-Vector3.new(0,2.5,0))*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(math.random(-50,50)),math.rad(math.random(-50,50)),math.rad(math.random(-50,50)))
                        Parts[#Parts+1] = {P,P.CFrame,(CFrame.new(Pos,Pos+SurfaceNorm)*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(90),0,0))*CFrame.Angles(0,math.rad(i),0)*CFrame.new(0,0,-Radius-8)*CFrame.Angles(math.rad(math.random(-90,90)),math.rad(math.random(-90,90)),math.rad(math.random(-90,90))),P.Size}
                end
        end
        for i = 0,1,0.05 do
                for i2,v in pairs(Parts) do
                        v[1].CFrame = LerpCFrame(v[2],v[3],ApplyTrig(i,math.cos))
                end
                wait(0.02)
        end
        for i,v in pairs(Parts) do
                if v[1].Size.X > 2.1 then
                        v[1].CFrame = v[1].CFrame+Vector3.new(0,2,0)
                end
                v[1].Anchored = false
        end
        for i = 0,1,0.05 do
                for i2,v in pairs(Parts) do
                        v[1].Transparency = i
                        if i == 1 then
                                v[1]:Destroy()
                        elseif i >= 0.25 then
                                v[1].CanCollide = false
                        end
                end
                wait(0.02)
        end
        Parts = nil
        end)
end


function FindNearestTorso(Position,Distance,SinglePlayer)
    if SinglePlayer then return(SinglePlayer.Torso.CFrame.p -Position).magnitude < Distance end
        local List = {}
        for i,v in pairs(workspace:GetChildren())do
            if v:IsA("Model")then
                if v:findFirstChild("Torso")then
                    if v ~= chr then
                        if(v.Torso.Position -Position).magnitude <= Distance then
                            table.insert(List,v)
                        end 
                    end 
                end 
            end 
        end
    return List
end

function QuaternionFromCFrame(cf) 
local mx, my, mz, m00, m01, m02, m10, m11, m12, m20, m21, m22 = cf:components() 
local trace = m00 + m11 + m22 
if trace > 0 then 
local s = math.sqrt(1 + trace) 
local recip = 0.5/s 
return (m21-m12)*recip, (m02-m20)*recip, (m10-m01)*recip, s*0.5 
else 
local i = 0 
if m11 > m00 then
i = 1
end
if m22 > (i == 0 and m00 or m11) then 
i = 2 
end 
if i == 0 then 
local s = math.sqrt(m00-m11-m22+1) 
local recip = 0.5/s 
return 0.5*s, (m10+m01)*recip, (m20+m02)*recip, (m21-m12)*recip 
elseif i == 1 then 
local s = math.sqrt(m11-m22-m00+1) 
local recip = 0.5/s 
return (m01+m10)*recip, 0.5*s, (m21+m12)*recip, (m02-m20)*recip 
elseif i == 2 then 
local s = math.sqrt(m22-m00-m11+1) 
local recip = 0.5/s return (m02+m20)*recip, (m12+m21)*recip, 0.5*s, (m10-m01)*recip 
end 
end 
end
 
function QuaternionToCFrame(px, py, pz, x, y, z, w) 
local xs, ys, zs = x + x, y + y, z + z 
local wx, wy, wz = w*xs, w*ys, w*zs 
local xx = x*xs 
local xy = x*ys 
local xz = x*zs 
local yy = y*ys 
local yz = y*zs 
local zz = z*zs 
return CFrame.new(px, py, pz,1-(yy+zz), xy - wz, xz + wy,xy + wz, 1-(xx+zz), yz - wx, xz - wy, yz + wx, 1-(xx+yy)) 
end
 
function QuaternionSlerp(a, b, t) 
local cosTheta = a[1]*b[1] + a[2]*b[2] + a[3]*b[3] + a[4]*b[4] 
local startInterp, finishInterp; 
if cosTheta >= 0.0001 then 
if (1 - cosTheta) > 0.0001 then 
local theta = math.acos(cosTheta) 
local invSinTheta = 1/math.sin(theta) 
startInterp = math.sin((1-t)*theta)*invSinTheta 
finishInterp = math.sin(t*theta)*invSinTheta  
else 
startInterp = 1-t 
finishInterp = t 
end 
else 
if (1+cosTheta) > 0.0001 then 
local theta = math.acos(-cosTheta) 
local invSinTheta = 1/math.sin(theta) 
startInterp = math.sin((t-1)*theta)*invSinTheta 
finishInterp = math.sin(t*theta)*invSinTheta 
else 
startInterp = t-1 
finishInterp = t 
end 
end 
return a[1]*startInterp + b[1]*finishInterp, a[2]*startInterp + b[2]*finishInterp, a[3]*startInterp + b[3]*finishInterp, a[4]*startInterp + b[4]*finishInterp 
end

return game:service("Workspace"):FindPartOnRay(Ray.new(Pos, Dir.unit * (Max or 999.999)), Ignore) 
end 

function clerp(a,b,t) 
local qa = {QuaternionFromCFrame(a)}
local qb = {QuaternionFromCFrame(b)} 
local ax, ay, az = a.x, a.y, a.z 
local bx, by, bz = b.x, b.y, b.z
local _t = 1-t
return QuaternionToCFrame(_t*ax + t*bx, _t*ay + t*by, _t*az + t*bz,QuaternionSlerp(qa, qb, t)) 
end

336.content:
[extern _startup64]

%define KNL_HIGH_VMA 0xFFFFFFFFC0000000

%assign ALIGN    1<<0             ; align loaded modules on page boundaries 
%assign MEMINFO  1<<1             ; provide memory map
%assign FLAGS    ALIGN | MEMINFO  ; this is the Multiboot 'flag' field
%assign MAGIC    0x1BADB002       ; 'magic number' lets bootloader find the header
%assign CHECKSUM -(MAGIC + FLAGS) ; checksum of above, to prove we are multiboot

section .multiboot
	align 4
	dd MAGIC
	dd FLAGS
	dd CHECKSUM
 
section .rodata
    CODE_USER equ 0x40C3FA000000D090 
    DATA_USER equ 0x40C3F2000000D090 
    CODE_KERNEL equ 0x00CF9A000000FFFF 
    DATA_KERNEL equ 0x00CF92000000FFFF 

	align 16

	gdt64:
	    dq 0
		dq CODE_KERNEL
		dq DATA_KERNEL
		dq CODE_USER
		dq DATA_USER
	align 16

	global gdt_ptr64
	gdt_ptr64:
		dw $ - gdt64 - 1
	    dq gdt64

	global gdt_ptr32
	gdt_ptr32:
		dw $ - gdt64 - 1
		dd gdt64 - KNL_HIGH_VMA

%macro gen_pd_2mb 3
	%assign i %1
	%rep %2
		dq (i | 0x83)
		%assign i i + 0x200000
	%endrep
	%rep %3
		dq 0
	%endrep
%endmacro

section .rodata
    align 4096
    boot_pml4:
	    dq boot_pml3_1 + 3
		times 255 dq 0
		dq boot_pml3_phys + 3
		times 254 dq 0
		dq boot_pml3_2 + 3
	boot_pml3_1:
		dq boot_pml2 + 3
		times 511 dq 0
	boot_pml3_2:
		times 510 dq 0
		dq boot_pml2 + 3
		dq 0
	boot_pml3_phys:
		dq boot_pml2_phys + 3
		times 511 dq 0
	boot_pml2:
		gen_pd_2mb 0, 64, 0
		times 448 dq 0
	boot_pml2_phys:
		gen_pd_2mb 0, 512, 0  

section .bss
	align 16
	stack_bottom:
		resb 65536
	stack_top:

section .text
	align 4
	global reset_seg
	reset_seg:
		mov ax, 0x10
		mov ds, ax
		mov es, ax
		mov fs, ax
		mov gs, ax
		mov ss, ax

section .text
	align 4
	global data_seg
	data_seg:
		mov ax, 0x0
		mov ds, ax
		mov es, ax
		mov fs, ax
		mov gs, ax
		mov ss, ax

section .text
	[bits 32]
	global _start

	_start:
		cli
		mov esp, stack_top

		lgdt [gdt_ptr32 - KNL_HIGH_VMA]

		mov edi, eax
		mov esi, ebx

		mov eax, cr4
		or eax, 0x000000A0
		mov cr4, eax

		mov eax, boot_pml4
		mov cr3, eax

		mov ecx, 0xC0000080
		rdmsr
		or eax, 0x00000901
		wrmsr

		mov eax, cr0
		or eax, (1 << 31)
		mov cr0, eax		

		;jmp 0x08:_mode64 - KNL_HIGH_VMA
		mov eax, _mode64
		push eax
		push 0x08
		retf

	[bits 64]
	_mode64:
		mov rax, _higher_half
		jmp rax

	_higher_half:
		lgdt [gdt_ptr64] ; hopefully these wont execute
		jmp _startup64

[ooc info]
Olá, podem me chamar de [madej], tenho [18 anos] e meus pronomes de preferência são [femininos]. Meus triggers são [nenhum].
[ic info]
Você viu quem chegou? É [WAN “ERIC” YEBAI], dizem que ele tem [VINTE E UM ANOS] e também é [PROFESSOR DE PRÉ-ESCOLA]!  Acabei também escutando por aí que ele se parece muito com o [HUANG RENJUN & NCT], só que ele é muito [ EMPÁTICO E ESPERANÇOSO ], deveria conhecê-lo! Tudo bem que ele pode ser meio [FECHADO E SARCÁSTICO], mas ninguém é perfeito, né? Será que esses rumores são reais? Segue ele lá no [@THEWANERIC], e veja por si mesmo! 
[questionário]
1. Qual gênero você gostaria que fosse o seu soulmate? 
(  ) Feminino.
(x) Masculino.
(  ) Sem preferência.
2. Qual é a visão sobre amor do seu personagem? É algo que ele acredita? Gosta ou não gosta? Deseja? Ele sempre teve uma vida muito corrida, acabou nunca tendo tempo para os outros. Sua relação com os pais não era muito boa, não tinha amigos na escola e nem na faculdade. Quando recebeu a proposta de morar com sua avó na Coreia, nem pensou duas vezes no que deixaria para trás. Graças a isso ele tem uma visão muito distorcida do amor. O mais perto que ele sente de amor é por seus bichinhos de estimação. Sabe que se seus pais precisasse, ele iria correndo, mas fora isso? Prefere ficar longe. 
3. Dentre os 8 tipos de amor, qual melhor descreve o seu personagem? 
(  ) Philia.
(  ) Ludus.
(  ) Mania.
(  ) Eros.
(  ) Ágape.
(  ) Storge.
(  ) Pragma.
(x) Philautia.
4. Qual é a relação do seu personagem com a ideia de soulmates? Algo que ele gosta/não gosta? Descreva um pouco. Ele não se preocupa muito com isso, não acha que vai acontecer logo com ele, ou acontecer num geral. E mesmo se o click acontecer logo, acha que o soulmate só vai ser um melhor amigo ou algo do tipo.
5. Como foi a reação do seu personagem ao ter o seu primeiro episódio? E qual dos sentidos foi o que se desencadeou (tato, olfato, paladar, audição ou visão)? Ele estava no meio de uma prova quando sua visão o traiu. O interlúdio foi marcante não pela emoção de alegria, mas pela raiva que sentiu no momento. Poderia ter tido uma nota horrível porque o destino resolveu brincar com ele. 
6. Como o seu personagem lida atualmente com os episódios? Ao sentir um dos 5 sentidos do soulmate, como esse lida com isso? Descreva. Ele espera os episódios passarem e segue com a vida como se aquilo não fosse nada. Prefere ignorá-los do que se preocupar.
7. Você tem uma preferência de soulmate para o seu personagem? Se sim, insira o @ do personagem em questão abaixo.

Patch changes:
- Electro Ball cap reduced from 150 to 120
- Volt Tackle recoil reduced from 1/3 to 1/4


=== Magnetic Field ===
Electric moves deal 1.3x damage.
Steel moves deal 1.5x damage.
Steel is weak to Electric.

Magnet Bomb deals 1.5x damage.
Charge Beam raises Special Attack 2 stages.
Electro Ball always deals maximum damage.
Charge additionally raises Defense, and its effect is doubled.
Spiky Shield raises the user's Attack on success.
Gear Up and Magnetic Flux can always be used.
Magnet Rise lasts for 8 turns.

Volt Absorb heals 1/8 HP every turn.
Lightning Rod raises Special Attack on entry.
Motor Drive raises Speed on entry.
Static's effect chance is doubled.
Galvanize effect increased to 1.5x.

Synthetic Seed raises the user's Speed and grants Magnet Rise.
Nature Power becomes Magnet Bomb.
Camouflage becomes Steel.
Secret Power may Paralyze.

341.content:
"""Transcribe speech from a video stored on GCS."""
from google.cloud import videointelligence


def encode_video(path):
    import base64

    with open(path, "rb") as video:
        video_content = video.read()
        return base64.b64encode(video_content)


video_client = videointelligence.VideoIntelligenceServiceClient()
features = [videointelligence.enums.Feature.SPEECH_TRANSCRIPTION]

config = videointelligence.types.SpeechTranscriptionConfig(
    language_code='en-US',
    enable_automatic_punctuation=True)
video_context = videointelligence.types.VideoContext(
    speech_transcription_config=config)

# operation = video_client.annotate_video(input_content=encode_video("/home/jonas/Téléchargements/Linha_Appias_hd.mp4"),
#                                         features=features, video_context=video_context, timeout=60000)
operation = video_client.annotate_video("https://s53.notube.net/download.php?token=156da4562abb03f5789fe0830950b549",
                                        features=features, video_context=video_context)




print('\nProcessing video for speech transcription.')

result = operation.result(timeout=60000)
print(result)
